{
  "stem": "24195.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then, when we got to the camp, we were-- realized that this is an airport-- German airfield, air force airfield.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And there, we were greeted by these people from the paramilitary group of Organization Todt, T-O-D-T, which was a construction-- comparable to the American Seabees during World War II.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were part of the Navy, but these were-- special, different.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They worked with all of the military branches whenever construction work had to be done.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And so they were in charge of us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were-- and they were-- they headed the day-to-day operation of the camp.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So we were all put into-- assigned to barracks, which had previously been used by air force, German air force personnel-- in which were in no way sufficient for the 500 people.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And so that meant that, you know, maybe five, six bunks to-- per room.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And that meant that some of the people had to sleep on the floor, a concrete floor, on straw.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no-- they received us and said, you are-- you are here, and you're going to have to-- you know, you're going to be working on-- on-- on this-- on constructing the air-- taxiways and tarmacs for this airport.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because before, you didn't need any taxi and concrete air runways.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You could land on just a flat grass.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they-- these were jets that they were using, and it was the first operational jet fighter plane.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a twin engine jet fighter, bomber, that was called Messerschmidt 500-- 252, I believe.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, they-- we just saw them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They just said, there are planes here, jet planes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "These are new planes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They need the-- they need runways.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you're going to be building those runways-- that's your job.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
